p43172
aVActivities are standalone entities, loosely coupled, as are Web pages
p43173
aVYou don't pass model objects between activities, just as you don't pass model objects between Web pages
p43174
aVThis does not mean that you cannot have a rich object model
p43175
aVHowever, just as Web pages are going back to a central server to manipulate the Web app's rich object model, activities will need to reach back to a central store to manipulate your rich object model
p43176
aVAnd, just as Web pages tend to pass around identifiers of objects, your activities can pass around identifiers of objects, so each activity can then access the proper object from the central store
p43177
aVWhether that central store is mediated by a  or via some singleton is up to you and would depend some on what that rich object model was really supposed to represent
